<subSubSection id="0DBE6518164BFF9E5F8EFF27FA68DEE8" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" type="key">
<keyStep id="FE502E36164BFF9E5F8EFF27FA68DDD1" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<paragraph id="451B3693164BFF9E5F8EFF27FA68DD88" blockId="3.[151,1437,220,741]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<keyLead id="FE5595A6164BFF9E5F8EFF27FA68DD88" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
1 Dark colour of pronotum more extensive, forming a large single mark, anteriorly expanded and including anterior half of lateral margins (
<figureCitation id="DD9F2A16164BFF9E5E7EFF02FE68DD02" box="[359,412,249,271]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[257,1324,189,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-16@4.[251,1335,181,1813]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Metallactus generosus Suffrian, 1866 (1), M. argentinensis Jacoby, 1907 (2): 1a–b: habitus; 1c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 1f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.4 mm]; 1g: spermatheca [0.6 mm]; 1h: antenna [1.6 mm]. 2a–b: habitus; 2c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 2f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.5 mm]; 2g: spermatheca [0.4 mm]; 2h: antenna [1.5 mm]. 1a–b: lectotype; 2a–b: lectotype. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule; sd: setose depression. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423975" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423975/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
a–b). Dorsal light colour including, in addition to elytral apical spot, a single generally semicircular patch spreading over posterolateral region of pronotum and anterolateral region of elytron. Frontal yellow spot small, with rounded lateral edges, generally not wider than 
<quantity id="825C9B76164BFF9E5D4AFECFFD6FDD47" box="[595,667,308,330]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation id="DD9F2A16164BFF9E5DB1FECFFD1ADD47" box="[680,750,308,330]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,1568,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-100@5.[151,1435,1560,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Frontal view. Metallactus generosus Suffrian, 1866 (a); M. argentinensis Jacoby, 1907 (b); M. nigroplagiatus new species (c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423981/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
). Pronotal sides slightly more convergent anterad, maximum width near posterior angles. Branches of endophallic sclerite IV distinctly arched dorsally, remarkably expanded apically to form a sickleshaped structure (
<figureCitation id="DD9F2A16164BFF9E5E95FE94FE38DD88" box="[396,460,367,389]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[257,1324,189,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-16@4.[251,1335,181,1813]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Metallactus generosus Suffrian, 1866 (1), M. argentinensis Jacoby, 1907 (2): 1a–b: habitus; 1c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 1f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.4 mm]; 1g: spermatheca [0.6 mm]; 1h: antenna [1.6 mm]. 2a–b: habitus; 2c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 2f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.5 mm]; 2g: spermatheca [0.4 mm]; 2h: antenna [1.5 mm]. 1a–b: lectotype; 2a–b: lectotype. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule; sd: setose depression. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423975" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423975/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Fig. 1f</figureCitation>
)......................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="82A44D10164BFF9E5B95FE94FA68DD88" authority="Suffrian, 1866" authorityName="Suffrian" authorityYear="1866" box="[1164,1436,367,389]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="generosus">
<emphasis id="77D0EA81164BFF9E5B95FE94FAF8DD89" box="[1164,1292,367,388]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">M. generosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="21354B62164BFF9E5A0BFE94FA68DD88" author="Suffrian, E." box="[1298,1436,367,389]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" pagination="1 - 483" refId="ref11454" refString="Suffrian, E. (1866) Zur Kenntnis der Sudamerikanischen Cryptocephalen. Linnaea Entomologica, 16, 1 - 483." type="journal article" year="1866">Suffrian, 1866</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="451B3693164BFF9E5F8EFE76FA68DDD1" blockId="3.[151,1437,220,741]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<keyLead id="FE5595A6164BFF9E5F8EFE76FA68DDD1" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">- Dark colour of pronotum less extensive, generally formed by two distinct longitudinal stripes, sometimes coalescing anteriorly but never reaching lateral margins of pronotum. Pronotal sides more regularly arched, maximum width close to midline. Branches of endophallic sclerite IV distinctly to slightly broadened at apex....................................... 2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="FE502E36164BFF9E5F8EFE1FFA68DEE8" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<paragraph id="451B3693164BFF9E5F8EFE1FFA68DE5C" blockId="3.[151,1437,220,741]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<keyLead id="FE5595A6164BFF9E5F8EFE1FFA68DE5C" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
2 Black elytral colouration formed by a median stripe generally enlarged in posterior half to reach the lateral margin, so that a distinct subcircular or subelliptic yellow spot is present on apical region (
<figureCitation id="DD9F2A16164BFF9E5CB9FDFAFC2DDE1A" box="[928,985,513,535]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[257,1324,189,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-16@4.[251,1335,181,1813]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Metallactus generosus Suffrian, 1866 (1), M. argentinensis Jacoby, 1907 (2): 1a–b: habitus; 1c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 1f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.4 mm]; 1g: spermatheca [0.6 mm]; 1h: antenna [1.6 mm]. 2a–b: habitus; 2c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 2f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.5 mm]; 2g: spermatheca [0.4 mm]; 2h: antenna [1.5 mm]. 1a–b: lectotype; 2a–b: lectotype. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule; sd: setose depression. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423975" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423975/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
a–b). Frontal yellow spot broader, with pointed lateral edges and clearly concave sides, generally between 0.7 and 
<quantity id="825C9B76164BFF9E5C7DFDE4FC59DE39" box="[868,941,543,564]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" unit="mm" value="1.2">1.2 mm</quantity>
wide (
<figureCitation id="DD9F2A16164BFF9E5CF6FDE4FBCCDE38" box="[1007,1080,543,565]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,1568,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-100@5.[151,1435,1560,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Frontal view. Metallactus generosus Suffrian, 1866 (a); M. argentinensis Jacoby, 1907 (b); M. nigroplagiatus new species (c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423981/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Fig. 4b</figureCitation>
). Branches of endophallic sclerite IV only moderately broadened distally (
<figureCitation id="DD9F2A16164BFF9E5D5BFDC7FD71DE5F" box="[578,645,572,594]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1837,1861]" captionTargetBox="[257,1324,189,1802]" captionTargetId="figure-16@4.[251,1335,181,1813]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Metallactus generosus Suffrian, 1866 (1), M. argentinensis Jacoby, 1907 (2): 1a–b: habitus; 1c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 1f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.4 mm]; 1g: spermatheca [0.6 mm]; 1h: antenna [1.6 mm]. 2a–b: habitus; 2c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.8 mm]; 2f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.5 mm]; 2g: spermatheca [0.4 mm]; 2h: antenna [1.5 mm]. 1a–b: lectotype; 2a–b: lectotype. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule; sd: setose depression. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423975" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423975/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Fig. 2f</figureCitation>
)........................................ 
<taxonomicName id="82A44D10164BFF9E5B60FDC6FA68DE5C" authority="Jacoby, 1907" authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1907" box="[1145,1436,572,594]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argentinensis">
<emphasis id="77D0EA81164BFF9E5B60FDC6FAEDDE5F" box="[1145,1305,573,594]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">M. argentinensis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="21354B62164BFF9E5A06FDC7FA68DE5C" author="Jacoby, M." box="[1311,1436,572,594]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" pagination="829 - 855" refId="ref11017" refString="Jacoby, M. (1907) Descriptions of new species of South-American beetles of the Cryptocephaline division of the Family Chrysomelidae. Proceedings of the General Meetings for Scientific Business of the Zoological Society of London, May- December, 1907, 829 - 855. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1907. tb 06961. x" type="journal article" year="1907">Jacoby, 1907</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="451B3693164BFF9E5F8EFDA1FA68DEE8" blockId="3.[151,1437,220,741]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
<keyLead id="FE5595A6164BFF9E5F8EFDA1FA68DEE8" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">
- Median elytral black stripe usually not widened in posterior half, and in any case not reaching lateral margin, so that light colour forms a continuous stripe along lateral region of the elytra from base to apex (
<figureCitation id="DD9F2A16164BFF9E5B08FD8CFBBDDE80" box="[1041,1097,631,653]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1439,1463]" captionTargetBox="[229,1342,213,1380]" captionTargetId="figure-38@5.[151,1435,181,1418]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. M. nigroplagiatus new species: a–b: habitus (lectotype, from type locality); c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.7 mm]; f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.5 mm]; g: spermatheca [0.4 mm]; h: antenna [1.6 mm]. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423979" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423979/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
a–b). Frontal yellow spot narrower, more irregularly shaped, generally not exceeding 
<quantity id="825C9B76164BFF9E5DA5FD6FFCF1DEA7" box="[700,773,660,682]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
width (
<figureCitation id="DD9F2A16164BFF9E5C56FD6FFC61DEA7" box="[847,917,660,682]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1983,2007]" captionTargetBox="[161,1428,1568,1949]" captionTargetId="figure-100@5.[151,1435,1560,1959]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 4. Frontal view. Metallactus generosus Suffrian, 1866 (a); M. argentinensis Jacoby, 1907 (b); M. nigroplagiatus new species (c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423981" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423981/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Fig. 4c</figureCitation>
). Branches of endophallic sclerite IV distinctly arched towards dorsal direction, remarkably expanded apically to form a sickle-shaped structure (
<figureCitation id="DD9F2A16164BFF9E5B5CFD4AFB72DECA" box="[1093,1158,689,711]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1439,1463]" captionTargetBox="[229,1342,213,1380]" captionTargetId="figure-38@5.[151,1435,181,1418]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. M. nigroplagiatus new species: a–b: habitus (lectotype, from type locality); c–e: median lobe of aedeagus in ventral (c), dorsal (d) and lateral (e) view [0.7 mm]; f: sclerites of endophallus in lateral view [0.5 mm]; g: spermatheca [0.4 mm]; h: antenna [1.6 mm]. scI–IV: sclerites I–IV of endophallus; ds: dorsal spicule. Square brackets: length of scale segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423979" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4423979/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">Fig. 3f</figureCitation>
).................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="82A44D10164BFF9E5B6FFD34FAD6DEE9" authority="Sassi, 2020" authorityName="Sassi" authorityYear="2020" box="[1142,1314,719,740]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Metallactus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroplagiatus" status="new species">
<emphasis id="77D0EA81164BFF9E5B6FFD34FAD6DEE9" box="[1142,1314,719,740]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="151">M. nigroplagiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="6CE357FA164BFF9E5A30FD34FA68DEE8" box="[1321,1436,719,741]" pageId="3" pageNumber="151" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
